Diagnosis. Body mostly light green; wings hyaline with green pterostigma, venation predominantly green, with brown pigmentation on the junctions; forewing with 1 AA elliptical, aa-ap vein, almost parallel to the posterior wing margin (
Hoffman 2002
). Male abdomen with intertergal membrane between the tergites III‒V invaginated, bilobed, each lobe with a single pore transversely elongated.
